I think we should end
with a martini, OK?

41:19.840 --> 41:22.440
So, how would anybody
like theirs?

41:22.440 --> 41:23.960
Shaken, not stirred. No?

41:23.960 --> 41:26.440
KLAXON

41:23.960 --> 41:26.440
What?! Oh.

41:28.520 --> 41:31.280
So, the thing is that shaking
a martini will ruin it,

41:31.280 --> 41:33.440
and I know this
cos I'm a martini fan, OK?

41:33.440 --> 41:35.560
So drinks like daiquiris,
they're shaken

41:35.560 --> 41:38.280
and the reason for that is that
the ice dilutes the sweetness.

41:38.280 --> 41:41.040
Martinis are not sweet,
so they don't need to be shaken.

41:41.040 --> 41:44.000
They're supposed to be served
as concentrated as possible.

41:44.000 --> 41:46.560
Unfortunately we can't drink
the original martinis

41:46.560 --> 41:48.520
that James Bond
is supposed to have had

41:48.520 --> 41:51.120
because one of the key ingredients
is no longer available.

41:51.120 --> 41:54.560
It's known as a Vesper Martini. It
was named after the first Bond girl,

41:54.560 --> 41:57.840
she was called Vesper Lynd.
Vespa's Italian for wasp.

41:57.840 --> 41:59.560
Did you know that? No, I didn't.

41:59.560 --> 42:01.760
Yes, hence the scooter.
The scooter, the Vespa.

42:01.760 --> 42:04.600
It sounds like a wasp.
Bzzzzzz! Wasp. You see?

42:04.600 --> 42:08.440
The Vesper Martini
contained gin and vodka

42:08.440 --> 42:11.160
and something called Kina Lillet.

42:11.160 --> 42:13.760
Doesn't sound pleasant, does it?
It would absorb a lot.

42:13.760 --> 42:16.480
You don't want THAT in your martini.

42:16.480 --> 42:19.400
Anyway, the trick is...to stir it.

42:19.400 --> 42:22.520
Have you got drinks there
for yourselves? Yes. Yes.

42:22.520 --> 42:26.320
OK. Just, um, pour out...
in tribute here.

42:26.320 --> 42:28.760
Ooh-hoo! OK.

42:28.760 --> 42:32.200
Do you know that Dick Van Dyke
was once asked by Cubby Broccoli

42:32.200 --> 42:35.880
if he wanted to take over
from Sean Connery in the role,

42:35.880 --> 42:39.400
and Dick Van Dyke reminded him
of his British accent as Bert,

42:39.400 --> 42:42.240
the Cockney chimney sweep
in Mary Poppins.

42:42.240 --> 42:45.040
It was generally thought
not to be a very good idea.

42:45.040 --> 42:47.880
Well, here we go.
Cheers. Cheers.

42:47.880 --> 42:50.760
AS SEAN CONNERY: Martinis are
better shtirred than shaken,

42:50.760 --> 42:54.080
and underpants
are better shilk than shatin.

42:54.080 --> 42:56.560
LAUGHTER

42:56.560 --> 42:59.000
APPLAUSE

43:00.400 --> 43:04.520
And, with that, it's the final dash
towards the scores!

43:04.520 --> 43:07.240
Top of the pack
with nine points,

43:07.240 --> 43:09.280
it's Alan! What?!

43:09.280 --> 43:12.520
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

43:14.520 --> 43:16.360
Second, with eight points,

43:16.360 --> 43:19.920
it's James!
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

43:19.920 --> 43:23.000
I couldn't even open a briefcase,
and who got beat by me?!

43:23.000 --> 43:24.480
Yes!

43:24.480 --> 43:27.280
Third with -2, Daliso!

43:24.480 --> 43:27.280
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

43:27.280 --> 43:30.320
CARIAD: Oh, no!

43:30.320 --> 43:33.840
And in last place with -15,
it's Cariad!

43:33.840 --> 43:36.320
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

43:41.680 --> 43:44.320
My thanks to James, Cariad,
Daliso and Alan, and I leave you

43:44.320 --> 43:47.400
with this secret sign-off
from Lucille Ball.

43:47.400 --> 43:50.320
The secret of staying young
is to live honestly,

43:50.320 --> 43:52.480
eat slowly and lie about your age.

43:52.480 --> 43:53.640
Goodnight.

43:53.640 --> 43:55.760
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE
